a)  √[5]{3x} + √[5]{3x}  
   = 1·√[5]{3x} + 1·√[5]{3x}  
   = (1 + 1)·√[5]{3x}  
   = 2√[5]{3x}

b)  3√[3]{9} − √[3]{9}  
   = 3·√[3]{9} − 1·√[3]{9}  
   = (3 − 1)·√[3]{9}  
   = 2√[3]{9}

So the simplified results are  
a) 2√[5]{3x}  
b) 2√[3]{9}.

Like radicals (same index and same radicand) add and subtract just the way like terms do: we keep the radical part and combine the numerical coefficients.

